/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Referencing_for_beginners" title=3D"Help:Refere=
ncing for beginners">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced ma=
terial may be challenged and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikip=
edia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence" title=3D"Wikipedia:Verifiability">re=
moved</a>.</span>  <span class=3D"date-container"><i>(<span class=3D"date">=
May 2014</span>)</i></span><span class=3D"hide-when-compact"><i> (<small><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" t=
itle=3D"Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove thi=
s message</a></small>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>For residents, there are two options for treating capital gains (shares,=
 bonds, interests, etc.).=20
It was introduced by President <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emm=
anuel_Macron" title=3D"Emmanuel Macron">Emmanuel Macron</a> as a key promis=
e of its campaign and is called the Pr=C3=A9l=C3=A8vement Forfaitaire Uniqu=
e =E2=80=93 PFU. The first option is a flat 30% rate. The second option is =
to opt for the former treatment whereby gains are taxed at 17.2% for "socia=
l contributions" and (if the instrument has been held for at least two year=
s) 60% of the gains are taxed as individual revenue (tax scale between 0=E2=
=80=9345%). The following year, 6.8% of the gains can be deducted from the =
tax base. For equities bought after 1 January 2018, the 60% reduction for 2=
-year long hold does not apply anymore.
</p><p>If shares are held in a special account (called a PEA), the gain is =
subject only to "social contributions" (17.2%) provided that the PEA is hel=
d for at least five years. The maximum amount that can be deposited in the =
PEA is =E2=82=AC150,000.
</p><p>The gain realized on the sale of a principal residence is not taxabl=
e. A gain realized on the sale of other real estate held at least 30 years,=
 however, is not taxable, although this will become subject to 15.5% social=
 security taxes as of 2012. (There is a sliding scale for non-principal res=
idence property owned for between 22 and 30 years.)
</p><p>Non-residents are generally taxable on capital gains realized on Fre=
nch real estate and on some French financial instruments, subject to any ap=
plicable double tax treaty. Social security taxes, however, are not usually=
 payable by non-residents. A French tax representative will be mandatory fo=
r non-residents who sell a property for an amount over 150.000 euros or who=
 own the real estate for more than 15 years.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Germany">Germany</h3><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gains_tax&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edit section: Germany"><span>edit<=
/span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1305433154"><table class=3D"box-Unreferenced_section plainlinks metadata am=
box ambox-content ambox-Unreferenced" role=3D"presentation"><tbody><tr><td =
class=3D"mbox-image"><div class=3D"mbox-image-div"><span typeof=3D"mw:File"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg" class=
=3D"mw-file-description"><img alt=3D"icon" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.=
org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/60px-Question_book-new.sv=
g.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"50" height=3D"39" class=3D"mw-file-eleme=
nt" data-file-width=3D"512" data-file-height=3D"399"></a></span></div></td>=
<td class=3D"mbox-text"><div class=3D"mbox-text-span">This section <b>does =
