ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gains_tax&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D57" title=3D"Edit section: Serbia"><span>edit</sp=
an></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Capital gains are subject to a 15% tax for residents and 20% for nonresi=
dents (based on the tax assessment).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-82" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_gains_tax#cite_note-8=
2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>82<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Slovakia">Slovakia</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gains_tax&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D58" title=3D"Edit section: Slovakia"><span>ed=
it</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Individuals pay 19% or 25% capital gains tax. They are also required to =
pay 14% health insurance from capital gains.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Slovenia">Slovenia</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gains_tax&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D59" title=3D"Edit section: Slovenia"><span>ed=
it</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Individuals pay tax at a tax rate of 27.5%. However, for every five year=
s of ownenership, the rate is reduced: 20% (after five years), 15% (after t=
en years), 10% (after fifteen years); after twenty years there is no tax. E=
xception is a tax rate of 40% which applies only to profit on the disposal =
of derivative in less than one year after purchasing it.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"South_Africa">South Africa<=
/h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gain=
s_tax&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D60" title=3D"Edit section: South Afri=
ca"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<p>For legal persons in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Afri=
ca" title=3D"South Africa">South Africa</a>, 80% of their net profit will a=
ttract CGT and for natural persons 40%. This portion of the net gain will b=
e taxed at their marginal tax rate. As an effective tax rate this means a m=
aximum effective rate of 18% (45% maximum marginal tax rate) for individual=
s is payable, and for corporate taxpayers a maximum of 22.4%. The annual in=
dividual and special trust exemption is R40 000.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"South_Korea">South Korea</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DCapital_gains_=
tax&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D61" title=3D"Edit section: South Korea"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>For individuals holding less than 3% of listed company, there is only 0.=
3% trade tax for sales of shares. Exchange traded funds are exempt from any=
 trade tax. For larger than 3% shareholders of listed companies or for sale=
s of shares in any unlisted company, capital gains tax in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea" title=3D"South Korea">South Korea</a> =
is 11% for tax residents for sales of shares in small- and medium-sized com=
panies. Rates of 22% and 33% apply in certain other situations.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-83" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ca=
pital_gains_tax#cite_note-83"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>83<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Those who have been resident in K=
orea for less than five years are exempt from capital gains tax on foreign =
assets.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-84" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Capital_gains_tax#cite_note-84"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>84<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
